    <note>Qi(1) Lun [134] Second son of Tongwen [3031]. Tongwen, according to Zeng Gong, was the Song's equivalent to Liu(3) Zongyuan [3605] of Tang as a teacher of the statesmen (shi) of his time. Wang(2) Yaozhen(1) [1919] was the father-in-law of Lun's grandson, Shidao [3030]. Lun was Lu(2) Zongdao's [8096] patron. Tongwen was a close friend of Teng(1) She's [1610] father, Teng(1) Zhibo [3839]. SHY:ZG, 27.41a-41b; SS, 306.11b-12b; Zeng Gong, WJ, 42.1a, 3a.</note>
